The '''Battle of Farrukhabad''' took place on [[November 14]] [[1803]], between a small [[United Kingdom|British]] force under [[Gerard Lake, 1st Viscount Lake|General Lake]], and an army of 60,000 [[Maratha]]s under [[Jeswunt Rao Holkar]]. Holkar was signally defeated with heavy losses. The British casualties were two killed and 20 wounded.

